DIV1.P:
They have a Recreation cer∣tainly
deriv'd from their An∣cestours,
viz: La Mora, anci∣ently
micare Digitis, at the first
it appeares but childishly ridi∣culous;
after better acquain∣tance,
a kinde of Conjuration;
Tis of force to binde the Fan∣cy;
yet the most illiterate are
best at the Game.

Palladius made this his Ma∣ster-piece;
for tis so contriv'd,
that it containes Geometri∣cally
a Round, a Crosse, and a
Square.
